<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910524-0182</DOCNO><DOCID>910524-0182.</DOCID><HL>   American Stores,   Albertson's Post Rise   In 1st-Period Profits   ----   A Wall Street Journal News Roundup</HL><DATE>05/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ABS ASC</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>IDAHO (ID)UTAH (UT)</RE><LP>   Two big grocery chains reported increases in profits fortheir first quarter.   American Stores Co. of Salt Lake City reported a 29%increase and Albertson's Inc. of Boise, Idaho, posted a 15%rise.</LP><TEXT>   American Stores said net income for its first quarterended May 4 increased to $35.9 million, or $1.04 a share,from $27.9 million, or 81 cents a share, a year ago. The$1.04-a-share quarterly profit approached the estimates ofthe most bullish analysts, who forecast earnings as much as$1.10 a share. The first-quarter results include a loss oftwo cents a share from the sale of assets, the company said.   The company cited lower interest expense from continuingdebt reduction and lower interest rates compared with lastyear for the rise in profit.   Sales were flat at $5.41 billion compared with $5.42billion a year ago. The company's drug store units, Sav-Onand Osco, reported a 27% rise in operating profit to $40.1million from $31.6 million a year ago. The company reportedflat sales at its grocery store chains, reflecting the impactof the recession.   &quot;Food customers are not buying snack foods and are tradingdown on cuts of meats,&quot; a spokesman asid.   American shares closed at $85.125, down 37.5 cents incomposite trading on the New York Stock Exchange.   Albertson's profit rose 15% to $58.7 million, or 44 centsa share, in the 13 weeks ended May 2, from $51.2 million, or38 cents a share, in the year-ago period. The company saidprofit was in line with expectations. Sales rose 8% to $2.16billion from $2 billion. The company attributed the gain to3.4% sales increase in samestore sales and increasedefficiency of distribution.   Albertson's stock closed at $45.25, down 50 cents, incomposite Big Board trading.</TEXT></DOC>